BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Arts
DESCRIPTION:DJing is one of the original elements of Hip Hop and is often 
 considered the first. Hip Hop began in the Bronx during the 1970s at comm
 unity block parties\, where DJs used turntables to bring people together 
 through music. Early pioneers like DJ Kool Herc introduced breakbeats by 
 looping the most rhythmic parts of records\, creating the foundation for 
 breaking and shaping how dancers and MCs interacted with the music.\nAs H
 ip Hop evolved\, DJing became the musical backbone of the culture. DJs pr
 ovide the beats for MCing\, set the tempo for dancers\, and control the e
 nergy of Hip Hop spaces by reading the crowd and responding in real time.
  Through techniques like scratching\, cutting\, and beat juggling\, DJs h
 elped define Hip Hop’s sound while preserving its history and passing dow
 n cultural knowledge.\nThis class introduces the basics of DJing and how 
 music shapes the dance experience. DJ Bascis will explain core concepts s
 uch as tempo\, rhythm\, and song structure\, helping students understand 
 how music guides movement and energy on the dance floor.\nParticipants wi
 ll learn how DJs choose music\, create smooth transitions\, and adjust th
 e vibe based on the room. \nThrough simple examples and live demonstratio
 ns\, students will build confidence in listening to music with intention.
  This can bewhether they are dancing\, freestyling\, or interested in DJi
 ng themselves.\nThis class is designed for beginners and college students
 \, with no prior DJ or music experience required.\n\nHosted by: Campus Ac
 tivities at Bloomfield\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https:/
 /montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12095722
DTEND:20260408T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260407T030159Z
DTSTART:20260408T183000Z
LOCATION:Talbott Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The DJ Academy: Music Matters 101
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12095722
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12095722
X-HOSTS:Campus Activities at Bloomfield
END:VEVENT
