CATEGORIES:Medium Size
DESCRIPTION:Hey Red Hawks your voice matters\, and we want to hear from yo
 u!\n \nEach year\, the Montclair State University Board of Trustees (BOT)
  hosts its Annual Tuition Hearing—a dedicated space for university commun
 ity members to share their thoughts\, ask questions\, and express any con
 cerns about potential increases in tuition\, housing\, and student fees f
 or the upcoming academic year.\n \nThis open forum is not just about list
 ening—it’s about understanding. During the hearing\, University leaders w
 ill provide insight into how tuition and fee decisions are made\, includi
 ng the factors that influence these important choices. You’ll gain a clea
 rer picture of the budgeting process and have the chance to directly enga
 ge with decision-makers.\n \nWhether you have a personal story to share\,
  a question you’ve been wanting to ask\, or simply want to learn more\, w
 e encourage you to attend and participate. Your perspective helps shape a
  better\, more inclusive student experience. All are welcome\n \n💬 Come 
 join the conversation. Be informed. Be heard. Be an Advocate\nIf you are 
 unable to attend the BOT meeting on Thursday\, April 9th or the listening
  sessions\, submit your comments and/or questions on tuition and fees to:
  Quentin Ocampo at ocampoq1@montclair.edu or Jameson Klinsky at klinskyj1
 @montclair.edu .\n\nHosted by: Bloomfield College Student Government Asso
 ciation (BCSGA)\, Campus Activities\, Civic & Voter Engagement\, Student 
 Government Association\, Inc.\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: 
 https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12388648
DTEND:20260409T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260407T030159Z
DTSTART:20260409T143000Z
LOCATION:University Hall 7th Floor
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Board of Trustees Tuition Hearing
