BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:ThoughtfulLearning
CATEGORIES:Academic/Educational
DESCRIPTION:Why Godzilla Still Matters: Montclair State Professor Jason Ab
 bott to Speak in Brooklyn\nDr. Jason Abbott\, Professor of Political Scie
 nce and International Relations at Montclair State University\, will deli
 ver a public lecture as part of the Lectures on Tap series in Brooklyn\, 
 New York.\n \nTitle: Godzilla: Japan\, Trauma\, and the Unkillable Monste
 rDate: Wednesday\, April 22\, 2026Time: 6:30 p.m. – 8:30 p.m. (Lecture be
 gins at 7:00 p.m.)Location: Bushwick\, Brooklyn\, NY (exact address provi
 ded upon registration)Please Register: https://www.eventbrite.com/e/lectu
 res-on-tap-godzilla-japan-trauma-and-the-unkillable-monster-tickets-19851
 35400421?aff=oddtdtcreator\n \nLectures on Tap is a public lecture series
  that brings professors\, experts\, and storytellers into informal venues
  to deliver accessible\, thought-provoking talks.\n \nIn this lecture\, D
 r. Abbott examines Godzilla as a cultural lens through which to understan
 d Japan’s postwar experience. Emerging in the shadow of Hiroshima and Nag
 asaki\, Godzilla has long served as a cinematic reflection of national tr
 auma\, nuclear anxiety\, and unresolved historical memory. The talk explo
 res why the figure of Godzilla reappears at moments of crisis and what th
 is enduring monster reveals about how societies process catastrophe and c
 onstruct collective memory.\n \nDrawing on examples across multiple films
  and historical periods\, the lecture considers how trauma is not simply 
 resolved\, but often reworked and reimagined over time.\nAgenda:6:30 p.m.
  – Doors open\; seating\, food\, and drinks available6:55 p.m. – Host int
 roduction7:00 p.m. – Lecture begins7:45 p.m. – Audience Q&A8:00 p.m. – In
 formal discussion and networking8:30 p.m. – Event concludes\n\nHosted by:
  College of Humanities and Social Sciences (CHSS)\n\nAdditional Informati
 on can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/1235448
 4
DTEND:20260423T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260407T030159Z
DTSTART:20260422T223000Z
LOCATION:OFF CAMPUS
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Why Godzilla Still Matters: Montclair State Professor Jason Abbott
  to Speak in Brooklyn
